reviews.text: A well known Chinese restaurant serving Cantonese cuisines with specialty in seafood dishes. Foods are in general nicely prepared but rather expensive. Average HK$500 per head is not unusual. Try the egg yolk prawns and the daily special soups, these are really tasty.

The taste is stable and good. The price is of course not cheap. A few staff can speak English. 
Need to book in advance.
Very good Chinese cuisine with delicious dishes.  Prices are relaively high but really worth it.
The food quality is above average. I love their roasted piglet with crispy skin.
The quality of food have improved, despite losing Michelin star

reviews.text: Great place for shopping with lots of shops and restaurants. Phase III is currently under renovation but surprisingly, it provides clear directory to guide you to your destination. However, the mall is extremely busy, packed with tourists and locals. Recommend to go on weekday.

parkview restaurant is good. the all day breakfast is good and the price is reasonable. the restaurant provide good food and service. the pumpkin cream soup and English sausage is delicious but the bacon is too salty!!🤗🤔
Consists of high end fashion shops. You can find maja, Sandro, Zara, coach, longchamp those kind of shop. They also have a snoopy land right next to it. Good to kill time.
Very good mall with lots of good brands. Have very good promotional offers for luxury skin care brands. Purchased Estee lauder skin care set at more than half off the price
Big Shopping centre very good . Many BIg shop standby here. Transport famlier and convenient.
